
= „Basisentscheid online und offline“, e-democracy tool for governance, participation and decicion-making tool used by the German Pirate Party after their abandonment of the [[Liquid Feedback]] tool

URL = http://wiki.piratenpartei.de/Basisentscheid [http://basisentscheid.piratenpartei.de/haeufige-fragen/ FAQ] 

Actual portal: https://beo.piratenpartei.de/

=Discussion=

Volker Grassmuck:

"The Pirates Germany have moved on to a new e-democracy tool called BEO, „Basisentscheid online und offline“. Reasons giving for dropping [[Liquid Feedback]] are: it was never approved for binding decisions, suffered from lack of interest and caused privacy concerns [http://kompass.im/2014/11/der-beo-fliegt-neues-elektronisches-demokratietool-der-piraten-ersetzt-das-unbeliebte-liquid-feedback/]

It’s used for binding decisions either as verified voter (Postident) pseudonymously online or secretly at the ballot-box or via postal mail. It seems like one-persons-one-vote. I don’t see anything on delegation."


